  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It was hypothesized that eating a meal slowly would lead to a lower meal energy intake and
      lesser feelings of hunger and desire to eat and higher levels of fullness after the meal
      compared to eating the same meal more quickly.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
